# Coding Standards

## Principles

- **Single responsibility**: One clear purpose per function, class, module
- **Explicit over implicit**: No magic, no hidden state
- **Fail fast**: Validate inputs, surface errors clearly
- **Document intent**: Comments explain why, not what

## Structure

```
// ❌ BAD - vague, no error handling
function process(doc) {
  return ocr(doc);
}

// ✅ GOOD - explicit, typed, handles failure
async function extractTextFromDocument(
  document: DocumentInput
): Promise<ExtractionResult> {
  if (!document.content) {
    throw new ValidationError('Document must have content');
  }
  const result = await ocrEngine.extract(document);
  return { text: result.text, confidence: result.confidence };
}
```

## Naming

- Functions: verbs (`extractText`, `validateDocument`)
- Types/Classes: nouns (`DocumentProcessor`, `ExtractionResult`)
- Booleans: `is*`, `has*`, `can*` prefixes

## Error Handling

- Use typed errors, not generic `Error`
- Include context (what failed, why)
- Log before rethrowing when appropriate
